title: The Best Defense of Abortion You've Never Heard...Or Haven't Heard Completely.
description:
In this video I do my best to explain Judith Jarvis Thomson's 'A Defense of Abortion.  The paper might be the most influential chunk of Philosophy done in the last 100 years.  You may have heard of 'The Violinist' argument that the paper contains, but you likely haven't heard the entirety of the argument.  It is really good and worth considering regardless of your position on abortion.

I also have a video about Don Marquis' 'Why Abortion is Immoral': https://youtu.be/I0o17IYX02M ,
which is likely the most influential paper ever written arguing for the wrongness of abortion.  If you care about the abortion issue, they are both worth a look.
See you in the comments!

title: Can we trust our beliefs if God doesn't exist? Lets examine a transcendental argument for God.
description:
In this video I take a look a version of a transcendental argument for the existence of God popularized by C.S. Lewis.  I have seen versions from @CrossExamined ,@mattslick ,@BraxtonHunter, Sye Ten Bruggencate  and @Daily_Dose_Of_Wisdom .  These arguments attempt to prove the existence of God by connecting god's existence to our ability to trust our beliefs.  With a little help from Elon Musk, a Bucket of Cat Pee, A chocolate donut, mutant theist Mank Slurek and mutant atheist Mallett Occonohunty (I hope someone takes the time to bring both these dudes into AI art existence). Ultimately, we will show that the very best these arguments can do is question whether or not Atheists can trust their beliefs...and we will have an answer for that question as well.

0:00 Intro
01:15 The Transcendental Argument
02:05 A substitution instance: Elon Musk is an unmarried man.
03:44 The Transcendental argument can't prove anything about existence.
06:14 Matt Slick, @SansDeity  and a bucket of cat pee.
10:20 @CosmicSkeptic  Frank Turkek, the worst fake British accent ever, chocolate and tar.
13:45 Trusting beliefs, Consistency, Self-Defeatery, Mank Slurek.
15:57 Mallett O'Connohunty, Trusting beliefs about the world.
18:18 Mank the Uber-theist's final objection: Beliefs from a supernatural perspective.
18:58 Mallet's final mic drop (Featuring make-pretend Brandon McGuire)
20:37 The final conclusion: We have proven that Atheists can only believe atheist things.

and

title: Does This Video Debunk Every Abortion Argument Part 3
description:
@MattWalsh claims to debunk every abortion argument.  Here we examine the last 5 arguments he addresses and determine whether or not his counter-arguments are good ones (Ill give you a hint, at least one of them is good).

0:00 Intro
0:26 "Women Have Reproductive Rights"
1:02 Conception & Reproduction: Semantic Straw Man
1:48 Weird Use of the Term "Reproduction"
3:22 'What about Rape and Incest"
4:49 A Big Mistake: Human Entity, Human Being, Person are Not Equivalent.
6:32 "Women Cannot Be Forced to Remain Pregnant, They Have Bodily Autonomy"
7:37 Matt Begs the Question: "Parent" and "Child"
8:12 Begging the question again, "Murder" Edition
9:01 "Fetuses Aren't Conscious, Therefore We Can Kill Them"
9:47 We Know Some Stuff About Consciousness
10:47 Some Stuff We Can Agree On About Consciousness
12:38 Murder Question Begging Again
12:46 Temporary Unconsciousness and the Limiting Principle
14:48 "Pro-Lifers are Just a Bunch of Men Trying to Boss Women Around"
15:30 Why Matt Gets One Right!!!
16:19 Conclusion
16:30 Reminder: I Am Analyzing Matts Arguments, I Did Not Make Any Claims Regarding the Rightness or Wrongness of Abortion
16:53 The Idiot Proof List
 

IDIOT PROOF LIST
1. In general, When people make the argument, “abortion laws violate women’s reproductive rights they are including pregnancy as part of the reproductive process.
2. When people are talking about sexual reproduction, they usually consider pregnancy to be part of reproduction. ***Find any sort of scientific or scientific or popular SECULAR discussion of reproduction that clearly considers reproduction to be finished at the moment of conception and win a prize!!!***
3. If there are any published, philosophical accounts that define a person as a human being (this means the two terms ‘person’ and ‘human’ are meaningful equivalent ie. synonyms ie. all and only humans are persons ie. human and person are bi-conditional) they are exceptionally rare (if they exist at all).  ***Find one and win a prize!!!*** 
4. There are more than 20 definitions of ‘person’ in the Oxford English Dictionary…Many of which do not include the term ‘human’ or ‘homo sapiens’.
5. Question begging arguments assume the truth of the conclusion to an argument or sub-argument.
6. We know some things about consciousness.
7. People have identified different kinds of consciousness (Reflective vs Phenomenal vs Access etc.) not just differing degrees of consciousness.
8. ‘Awareness’ is a pretty darned conventional definition of consciousness (specifically phenomenal consciousness).
9. Nagel’s account of consciousness, “there is something that it is like’, is generally considered by philosophers of mind  to be an adequate, introductory explanation of phenomenal consciousness.
10. There is no scientific or evidence based reason to believe there is something that it is like to be a zygote.

title: Matt Walsh Abortion Short Revisited: A More Thorough Explanation That Considers Viewer Comments
description:
Let's try this again!   In this video I revisit a short by @MattWalsh.  There was a bunch of discussion in the comments section of the last video and with your help, I think I was able to do a little better job of thoroughly explaining the best analysis of the argument that I've got.

In this video you will get a more thorough explanation of what I think is going on with the argument from this short by Matt Walsh .  In the short, Matt argues that 'leftist' arguments for 'abortion rights' are hollow because very few leftists have addressed the following sorts of questions:  If rights are merely social constructs, then isn't the case that whatever the government decides are the rights of the people are the rights of the people? title: PROOF GOD DOES NOT EXIST??? The Problem of Evil. #God  #Faith #philosophy #evil #atheism
description:
In this video we will take a look at a simplified version of an argument that  J.L.  Mackie gave in Evil and Omnipotence.  In that paper he attempts to prove that God does not exist on the grounds that God would not allow the evil we find in the world.  I won't promise a definitive conclusion as to whether or not he succeeds in proving God doesn't exist, but I will show that a version of Mackie's argument  proves that a handful of popular 'Free Will Defenses'  fail...and we will see Dr. Craig 'Owning' himself ;).
